{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"It's pretty simple. There are nine, sort of, rules"},{"time":3000,"text":"that I discovered after 35 years of rock climbing."},{"time":7000,"text":"Most of them are pretty basic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":11000,"text":"Number one: don't let go --"},{"time":14000,"text":"very sure success method."},{"time":16000,"text":"But really, truly -- often you think about"},{"time":19000,"text":"letting go way before your body does."},{"time":21000,"text":"So hang in there,"},{"time":23000,"text":"and you come up with some pretty peculiar solutions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27000,"text":"Number two: hesitation is bad."},{"time":29000,"text":"This is a friction climb, up in Tuolumne Meadows,"},{"time":32000,"text":"in the Yosemite high country."},{"time":34000,"text":"Friction climbing doesn't have any sort of hard positive edges."},{"time":38000,"text":"You're climbing on little dimples and nubbins in the rock."},{"time":42000,"text":"The most friction you have is when you first put your hand"},{"time":46000,"text":"or your foot on the rock."},{"time":49000,"text":"And then from that point on, you're basically falling."},{"time":53000,"text":"So momentum is good. Don't stop."}]},{"cues":[{"time":56000,"text":"Rule number three: have a plan."},{"time":58000,"text":"This is a climb called the Naked Edge,"},{"time":60000,"text":"in El Dorado Canyon, outside of Boulder."},{"time":62000,"text":"This climber is on the last pitch of it."},{"time":65000,"text":"He's actually right about where I fell."},{"time":67000,"text":"There is about 1,000 feet of air below him."},{"time":70000,"text":"And all the hard pitches are actually below him."},{"time":73000,"text":"Often what happens is"},{"time":75000,"text":"you're planning so hard for like,"},{"time":77000,"text":"\"How do I get through the hardest part? How do I get through the hardest part?\""},{"time":80000,"text":"And then what happens?"},{"time":82000,"text":"You get to the last pitch. It's easy."},{"time":84000,"text":"And you're completely flamed out. Don't do it."},{"time":87000,"text":"You have to plan ahead to get to the top."}]},{"cues":[{"time":90000,"text":"But you also can't forget that each individual move"},{"time":93000,"text":"you have to be able to complete."},{"time":95000,"text":"This is a climb called the Dike Route,"},{"time":97000,"text":"on Pywjack Dome, up in the Yosemite high country."},{"time":101000,"text":"The interesting thing about this climb is it's not that hard."},{"time":104000,"text":"But if you're the leader on it,"},{"time":106000,"text":"at the hardest move, you're looking at about 100 foot fall,"},{"time":110000,"text":"onto some low angle slabs."},{"time":112000,"text":"So you've got to focus."},{"time":114000,"text":"You don't want to stop in the middle like"},{"time":117000,"text":"Coleridge's Kubla Kahn."},{"time":119000,"text":"You've got to keep going."}]},{"cues":[{"time":121000,"text":"Rule number five: know how to rest."},{"time":123000,"text":"It's amazing. The best climbers"},{"time":125000,"text":"are the ones that in the most extreme situations"},{"time":128000,"text":"can get their bodies into some position"},{"time":130000,"text":"where they can rest,"},{"time":132000,"text":"regroup, calm themselves, focus,"},{"time":135000,"text":"and keep going."},{"time":139000,"text":"This is a climb in the Needles, again in California."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141000,"text":"Fear really sucks because what it means is"},{"time":143000,"text":"you're not focusing on what you're doing."},{"time":146000,"text":"You're focusing on the consequences of"},{"time":148000,"text":"failing at what you're doing"},{"time":151000,"text":"because any given move should require"},{"time":153000,"text":"all your concentration and thought processes"},{"time":158000,"text":"to execute it effectively."}]},{"cues":[{"time":160000,"text":"One of the things in climbing is, most people"},{"time":163000,"text":"sort of take it straight on. And they follow the most obvious solution."},{"time":167000,"text":"This is the Devils Tower in Wyoming,"},{"time":170000,"text":"which is a columnar basalt formation"},{"time":173000,"text":"that most of you probably know from \"Close Encounters.\""},{"time":176000,"text":"With this, typically crack climbers"},{"time":178000,"text":"would put their hands in and their toes in"},{"time":180000,"text":"and just start climbing."},{"time":182000,"text":"The cracks are too small to get your toes into"},{"time":185000,"text":"so the only way to climb is using your fingertips"},{"time":188000,"text":"in the cracks,"},{"time":190000,"text":"and using opposing pressure"},{"time":192000,"text":"and forcing yourself up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":195000,"text":"Rule number eight: strength doesn't always equal success."},{"time":198000,"text":"In the 35 years I've been a climbing guide"},{"time":200000,"text":"and taught on indoor walls, and stuff like that,"},{"time":202000,"text":"the most important thing I've learned"},{"time":204000,"text":"was, guys will always try to do pull-ups."},{"time":207000,"text":"Beginning guys, it's like, they thrash, they thrash,"},{"time":209000,"text":"they get 15 feet up --"},{"time":211000,"text":"and they can do about 15 pull-ups right --"},{"time":213000,"text":"And then they just flame out."},{"time":215000,"text":"Women are much more in balance"},{"time":217000,"text":"because they don't have that idea"},{"time":220000,"text":"that they're going to be able to do 100 pull-ups."},{"time":222000,"text":"They think about how to get the weight over their feet"},{"time":225000,"text":"because it's sort of natural -- they carry you all day long."},{"time":228000,"text":"So balance is really critical,"},{"time":230000,"text":"and keeping your weight on your feet,"},{"time":232000,"text":"which is your strongest muscle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":234000,"text":"And of course there is rule number nine."},{"time":236000,"text":"I came up with rule number nine after"},{"time":238000,"text":"I actually didn't plan for a fall,"},{"time":240000,"text":"and went about 40 feet and cracked a rib."},{"time":243000,"text":"Once you get to that point where you know it's going to happen,"},{"time":246000,"text":"you need to start thinking about how you're going to let go"},{"time":249000,"text":"because that is the critical piece"},{"time":252000,"text":"of not getting hurt --"},{"time":254000,"text":"how you're going to fall onto the rope,"},{"time":258000,"text":"or if you're climbing without a rope,"},{"time":260000,"text":"fall to a place where you can actually control the fall."},{"time":264000,"text":"So don't hang on till the bitter end."},{"time":267000,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":269000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}